HEADWORD: bittercress
<hw>bit"ter*cress</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>any of various herbs of the
genus Cardamine, having usually pinnate leaves and racemes of white,
pink or purple flowers; cosmopolitan except in the Antarctic.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bitter cress.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bitterful</ent>⟦br⟧
